annotationA: Transcription initiation factor IIE subunit beta; Recruits TFIIH to the initiation complex and stimulates the RNA polymerase II C-terminal domain kinase and DNA-dependent ATPase activities of TFIIH. Both TFIIH and TFIIE are required for promoter clearance by RNA polymerase
annotationB: Suppressor of stem-loop mutation, isoform A; Zinc ion binding; core RNA polymerase binding transcription factor activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; transcriptional open complex formation at RNA polymerase II promoter; nucleotide-excision repair; promoter clearance from RNA polymerase II promoter; transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter
